snippet: The deal between longtime enemies among the Islamists and the secular old guard aims to put in place an independent caretaker government until new elections next year.
abstract: Tunisia breaks new ground with political deal between longtime enemies among the Islamists and the secular old guard; agreement aims to put in place an independent caretaker government until new elections in 2014, marking first time Islamists have agreed in face of rising public anger to step back from power gained at ballot box.
lead_paragraph: The deal between longtime enemies among the Islamists and the secular old guard aims to put in place an independent caretaker government until new elections next year.

headline.main: A Political Deal in a Deeply Divided Tunisia as Islamists Agree to Yield Power
